item.title: So, some guy released an hour of Battlefront 3 gameplay...
item.dc:creator: lunertexcosmo
item.description:
Why does George Lucas and all of his other companies intentionally go against what his fans want?

Fans: Battlefront 3!

Lucas: How about some Force Unleashed?

Fans: Battlefront 3!!!

Lucas: Force Unleashed 2!

Fans: BATTLEFRONT 3!

Lucas: Old Republic.

Fans: BATTLEFRONT 3. But Old republic is actually kind of cool.

Lucas: 1313… and Kinect.

It just makes me really disappointed. I think it would be really cool if the community were to make Battlefront 3. But they’re not exactly Valve and I have a feeling that it would end in lawsuits.

item.dc:creator: MRPolo
item.description:
W-w-w-wait… Is that the highest an Xbox can take? Just kidding. Anyway, I never was a Star Wars fan and am still not and this is just Battlefield, ripped off by Lucas Arts. Did I get something wrong here? I understand the whole idea of pre-alpha stage and “Actually getting the game to work” but I have seen far better pre-alpha stages then this. There is a big leap between being able to run the game and being able to run the game with 12 fps…
